# Deployment — GitHub Pages

Every web app deploys to GitHub Pages under a specific sub-route. The root (`/`) is a Primer-styled landing page listing all apps.

## URL Structure

```
https://<user>.github.io/primer-guidy/          → Landing page (app list)
https://<user>.github.io/primer-guidy/core/      → core-web app
https://<user>.github.io/primer-guidy/login/     → login-web app
```

## Requirements per Web App

### 1. Rsbuild — `assetPrefix` and `base`

Every app's `rsbuild.config.ts` MUST set the correct base path for production:

```typescript
const BASE_PATH = '/primer-guidy/core/'

export default defineConfig({
  output: {
    assetPrefix: BASE_PATH,
  },
})
```

### 2. TanStack Router — `basepath`

The router MUST use the same base path:

```typescript
export const router = createRouter({
  routeTree,
  basepath: '/primer-guidy/core/',
  context: { queryClient },
})
```

### 3. SPA Fallback — `404.html`

GitHub Pages does not support SPA routing natively. Each app MUST include a `404.html` redirect script in its build output to handle client-side routing.

## Landing Page

- Lives at the root of the deployed site
- Generated automatically during CI from `.github/pages/generate.ts`
- Uses `@primer/css` (CDN) for consistent design with the rest of the monorepo
- Lists ALL web apps with name, description, and link

## CI/CD — GitHub Actions

Workflow `.github/workflows/deploy.yml` with 5 jobs:

```
install → analyze ──────┐
        → test-unit ────┤→ deploy-pages → deploy-firebase
        → test-e2e ─────┘
```

| Job | Runs | What |
|-----|------|------|
| `install` | Always | Install deps, cache `node_modules` |
| `analyze` | Always | `tsc --noEmit`, ESLint, Stylelint, Prettier |
| `test-unit` | Always | Vitest unit + integration tests |
| `test-e2e` | Always | Playwright E2E tests |
| `deploy-pages` | main only, after 3 pass | Build, generate landing, deploy to GH Pages |
| `deploy-firebase` | main only, after GH Pages | Placeholder for future Firebase deployment |

- PRs run `analyze`, `test-unit`, `test-e2e` — no deploy
- Pushes to `main` run everything including deploy

## Adding a New App

When creating a new web app:

1. Set `assetPrefix` in `rsbuild.config.ts`
2. Set `basepath` in `router.ts`
3. Register it in `.github/pages/apps-registry.json`
4. Add `dev:<name>` script in root `package.json`
5. Add copy step in `deploy.yml` under "Assemble deploy output"
6. CI handles the rest automatically

## Rules

- NEVER deploy without the correct `assetPrefix` — assets will 404
- NEVER hardcode absolute paths in components — use relative or router-aware paths
- The landing page MUST always be up-to-date with all current apps
- ALL deployments go through CI — no manual deploys
